Fun history facts: In US Constitution 1.0, whoever came in second got to be VP, regardless of party. Jefferson and Burr were the first to run as a unified ticket. Jefferson and Burr ended up tied in the election, with the incumbent, Adams, coming in third, so it went to the House of Representatives, and things got a bit crazy. Jefferson won after 36 ballots, and never trusted Burr after that, believing that he had been campaigning for the top spot all along.

Fans of the musical need to know that Hamilton was actually the villain of the story.

